Description: Body sherd of Chian Wild Goat Style pottery chalice; white slip; interior glazed streaky brown; possible traces of bands in added white at top of sherd; exterior: part of large maeander framing ornament; below, two narrrow bands.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0069) (phase 2)
